            <h3 class="beta">WITNESS</h3>

            <p>Neon and <a href="https://witness.org/" rel="external">WITNESS</a> have a shared interest in the history-making power of images. WITNESS works to train citizen journalists in capturing visual evidence of human rights violations. Neon and WITNESS have <a href="https://medium.com/neon-blog/changing-the-future-of-human-rights-with-video-technology-fe83402d602e" rel="me">partnered</a> to think about how video is changing the future of human rights. Read a write up of our discussion on our <a href="https://medium.com/neon-blog/changing-the-future-of-human-rights-with-video-technology-fe83402d602e" rel="me">blog</a> or on <a href="http://www.bloombergview.com/articles/2015-02-27/benner-on-tech-surveillance-privacy-ello-uber-and-ibm" rel="external">Bloomberg View</a>.</p>

